# .clinerules

## Standard Workflow

After making any changes to JavaScript/TypeScript files:
1. Run `pnpm lint:fix` to automatically fix linting and formatting issues
2. Confirm there are no errors before completing the task

## JavaScript/TypeScript Standards

### Function Declarations
- Always use `const` with arrow functions
- Never use the `function` keyword
- Example:
```javascript
  const handleClick = () => {
    // code here
  };
```

### Exports
- Use a single export statement at the end of the file
- Group all exports together
- Never use inline exports
- Example:
```javascript
  const ComponentA = () => {
    // code
  };
  
  const ComponentB = () => {
    // code
  };
  
  const helper = () => {
    // code
  };
  
  // Single export at the end
  export { ComponentA, ComponentB, helper };
```

### Imports
- Organize imports: external packages first, then internal modules
- Use named imports whenever possible
- Group imports by category
- Example:
```javascript
  // External packages
  import React from 'react';
  import { useState, useEffect } from 'react';
  
  // Internal modules
  import { helper } from './utils';
  import { ComponentA } from './components';
```

## Code Quality

- Ensure all code follows Biome rules
- No console.logs in production code
- Proper error handling in all async functions

## Component File Structure

Every component lives in its own folder under `src/components/`. Shared building blocks live under `src/components/base/`.

```
ComponentName/
  styled.ts    ← styled-components (internal, never public API)
  index.tsx    ← public RN component (entry point)
```

The public API is re-exported from `src/components/index.ts`. Only `ComponentName` and `ComponentProps` are exported — never `Styled*` pieces.

### `styled.ts`

- Contains all styled-components, prefixed with `Styled` (e.g. `StyledButton`, `StyledCard`).
- Props that drive styles use a `Styled*` interface when they differ from the public API (e.g. `StyledButtonProps`, `StyledCardProps`).
- Uses theme tokens from `src/theme` — never hardcoded values.
- Exports only styled pieces and their prop types:

```tsx
interface StyledCardProps {
  radius?: BorderRadiusToken;
  bg?: ColorToken;
}

const StyledCard = styled.View<StyledCardProps>`...`;

export type { StyledCardProps };
export { StyledCard };
```

### `index.tsx`

- Defines the public component (PascalCase, no `Styled` prefix).
- Defines `ComponentProps` — the full public API. May extend other props (`PaddingProps`), add `children`, or include business-logic props not passed to styled components.
- Applies defaults, composes other components, and handles logic.
- Never re-exports styled components.

```tsx
export type { ComponentProps };
export { Component };
```

### Patterns

**Thin wrapper** — styled props live in `styled.ts`, `index.tsx` adds `children`:

```tsx
// styled.ts
interface ContainerProps { direction?: FlexDirectionToken; ... }
const StyledContainer = styled.View<ContainerProps>`...`;

// index.tsx
interface ContainerComponentProps extends ContainerProps {
  children?: ReactNode;
}

const Container = ({ children, ...props }: ContainerComponentProps) => (
  <StyledContainer {...props}>{children}</StyledContainer>
);

export type { ContainerComponentProps as ContainerProps };
export { Container };
```

**Composition with Padding** — styled handles visuals, `Padding` handles spacing:

```tsx
// styled.ts — only visual props
interface StyledCardProps { radius?: BorderRadiusToken; bg?: ColorToken; }
const StyledCard = styled.View<StyledCardProps>`...`;

// index.tsx — public props extend PaddingProps
interface CardProps extends PaddingProps {
  radius?: BorderRadiusToken;
  bg?: ColorToken;
}

const Card = ({ padding = 'md', radius, bg, children, ...paddingProps }: CardProps) => (
  <StyledCard radius={radius} bg={bg}>
    <Padding padding={padding} {...paddingProps}>{children}</Padding>
  </StyledCard>
);
```

**Business logic** — props split between styled (visual) and index (behavior):

```tsx
// styled.ts — only props consumed by styles
interface StyledButtonProps { bg?: ColorToken; disabled?: boolean; ... }

// index.tsx — full public API
interface ButtonProps extends PaddingProps {
  label: string;
  onPress: () => void;
  loading?: boolean;
  ...
}
```

**Base components** (`src/components/base/`) — same folder pattern. `index.tsx` may resolve shorthand props before passing resolved values to `styled.ts` (see `Padding`).

Components with no styled-components skip `styled.ts` and live entirely in `index.tsx`.

## Tests

- Use the Arrange/Act/Assert pattern in every test
- Separate each section with a blank line and a comment (`// Arrange`, `// Act`, `// Assert`)
- Declare inputs in Arrange, never inline in Act
- Example:
```typescript
  it('does something', () => {
    // Arrange
    const input = { a: 1 };

    // Act
    const result = doSomething(input);

    // Assert
    expect(result).toBe(true);
  });
```